title: Thursday's boys' soccer roundup: West York's Prego notches hat trick
text:
Posted: 10/15/2015 09:24:28 PM EDT 
Here are Thursday's York/Adams boys' soccer results. Check back often for updates. 
WEST YORK 8, DOVER 3 >> John Prego scored a hat trick and Ben Olivier added two goals in the Bulldogs' victory. at West York 
Dover goals — Travis Hill, Robert Maze, David Trimmer. 
West York goals — John Prego 3, Ben Olivier 2, Aidan Clark, Nick Renda, Eddy Rodriguez. 
West York assists — Kenton Meckley 3, Josh May, Renda, Rodriguez. 
Shots on goal — Do 5. WY 11. 
Goalies — Do, Nathaniel Hamme (3 saves). WY, Darian McCauley (1 save), Cameron Goodling (1 save). 
GETTYSBURG 6, KENNARD-DALE 0 >> Adam Yingling and Drew Riggle each scored twice to lead the Warriors in the home win over the Rams. Yingling now has 51 career goals. 
Gettysburg's Matt Yingling added a goal and assist. Gettysburg
